                            <li><a href="string-literal.html">Strings</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </nav>
                </aside>

                <article class="content">
                    <section class="intro">
                        <div class="tag-container">
                            <span class="tag">Core Concept</span>
                            <span class="tag">Type System</span>
                            <span class="tag">Fundamentals</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="lead">CURSED comes with all the basic types you need to slay your coding projects. Let's get into these core types that are giving main character energy!</p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h3>Boolean Type</h3>
                        <pre><code><span class="comment">fr fr Boolean type: lit</span>
<span class="keyword">sus</span> isValid lit = <span class="keyword">based</span>  <span class="comment">fr fr true</span>
<span class="keyword">sus</span> isEmpty lit = <span class="keyword">sus</span>  <span class="comment">fr fr false</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Boolean operations</span>
<span class="keyword">sus</span> result lit = isValid && !isEmpty  <span class="comment">fr fr AND with NOT</span>
<span class="keyword">sus</span> anyTrue lit = isValid || isEmpty  <span class="comment">fr fr OR</span></code></pre>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h3>Numeric Types</h3>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Type</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                    <th>Range</th>
                                    <th>Example</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>smol</code></td>
                                    <td>8-bit integer</td>
                                    <td>-128 to 127</td>
                                    <td><code>sus age smol = 25</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>mid</code></td>
                                    <td>16-bit integer</td>
                                    <td>-32,768 to 32,767</td>
                                    <td><code>sus count mid = 1000</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>normie</code></td>
                                    <td>32-bit integer</td>
                                    <td>-2^31 to 2^31-1</td>
                                    <td><code>sus population normie = 8000000</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>thicc</code></td>
                                    <td>64-bit integer</td>
                                    <td>-2^63 to 2^63-1</td>
                                    <td><code>sus bigNum thicc = 9223372036854775807</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>snack</code></td>
                                    <td>32-bit float</td>
                                    <td>IEEE-754</td>
                                    <td><code>sus price snack = 9.99</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><code>meal</code></td>
                                    <td>64-bit float</td>
                                    <td>IEEE-754</td>
                                    <td><code>sus pi meal = 3.14159265359</code></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-title">numeric_operations.csd</div>
                            <pre><code><span class="comment">fr fr Integer literals</span>
sus x normie = 42       <span class="comment">fr fr decimal (base 10)</span>
sus y normie = 0x2A     <span class="comment">fr fr hexadecimal (base 16)</span>
sus z normie = 0o52     <span class="comment">fr fr octal (base 8)</span>
sus b normie = 0b101010 <span class="comment">fr fr binary (base 2)</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Floating point literals</span>
sus pi meal = 3.14159
sus sci snack = 6.022e23  <span class="comment">fr fr scientific notation</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Arithmetic operations</span>
sus sum = x + y         <span class="comment">fr fr addition</span>
sus diff = x - y        <span class="comment">fr fr subtraction</span>
sus product = x * y     <span class="comment">fr fr multiplication</span>
sus quotient = x / y    <span class="comment">fr fr division</span>
sus remainder = x % y   <span class="comment">fr fr modulo (remainder)</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h3>Character Type</h3>
                        <p>The <code>sip</code> type represents a single Unicode character (rune):</p>
                        
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-title">character_examples.csd</div>
                            <pre><code><span class="comment">fr fr Character literals use single quotes</span>
sus letter sip = 'A'
sus emoji sip = '💀'  <span class="comment">fr fr Unicode characters are fully supported</span>
sus newline sip = '\n'  <span class="comment">fr fr Escape sequences</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Character operations</span>
sus isUpper lit = letter >= 'A' && letter <= 'Z'
sus lowercase sip = letter + 32  <span class="comment">fr fr Convert uppercase ASCII to lowercase</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                        
                        <p>For more details on the character type, check out the <a href="sip-character-type.html">sip character documentation</a>.</p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h3>String Type</h3>
                        <p>The <code>tea</code> type represents text strings:</p>
                        
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-title">string_examples.csd</div>
                            <pre><code><span class="comment">fr fr String literals use double quotes</span>
sus greeting tea = "Hello, World!"
sus empty tea = ""  <span class="comment">fr fr Empty string</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Multi-line strings</span>
sus poem tea = "Roses are red\nViolets are blue\nCURSED is fire\nAnd so are you"

<span class="comment">fr fr String concatenation</span>
sus name tea = "bestie"
sus message tea = "What's good, " + name + "?"</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        
                        <p>For more string operations, check out the <a href="stringz.html">stringz package</a> documentation.</p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h3>Type Conversion</h3>
                        <p>CURSED requires explicit type conversions between different types:</p>
                        
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-title">type_conversion.csd</div>
                            <pre><code><span class="comment">fr fr Numeric conversions</span>
sus small smol = 100
sus medium normie = normie(small)  <span class="comment">fr fr Smaller to larger type</span>

sus large thicc = 1000000
sus truncated normie = normie(large)  <span class="comment">fr fr Larger to smaller type (possible data loss)</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Integer to floating-point</span>
sus count normie = 42
sus float snack = snack(count)  <span class="comment">fr fr normie -> snack</span>

<span class="comment">fr fr Floating-point to integer (truncates decimal portion)</span>
sus pi meal = 3.14159
sus rounded normie = normie(pi)  <span class="comment">fr fr becomes 3</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </section>

